  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/noncannulated-material-inputs",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis on Ti-6Al-4V material input parameters",
    "description": "Elastic modulus (E = 114 +/- 8 GPa), yield strength (Sy = 880 +/- 45 MPa), and tangent modulus (Et = 1.1 +/- 0.3 GPa) were each varied across their 95% confidence intervals derived from coupon testing of Batch A material. Construct stiffness QoI showed less than 3.2% variation across the full E range; yield force QoI showed up to 7.1% variation with Sy at its lower bound; force at 40 mm displacement was most sensitive to Et, varying by up to 9.8% — remaining within the pre-established 10% acceptance bound at the 95th percentile. These results justify accepting the wide material uncertainty as residual risk rather than requiring additional coupon testing."
  },
